abstract: Professors are tasked with asking hard questions about the country’s innovation and supply chains.
snippet: Professors are tasked with asking hard questions about the country’s innovation and supply chains.
lead_paragraph: Erica R.H. Fuchs argued so persuasively that the United States needs to get better at assessing its strengths and weaknesses in critical technologies that when the federal government finally agreed with her, she was picked to do it. “I talked myself into this job,” she said with a laugh.

abstract: The Shoggoth, a character from a science fiction story, captures the essential weirdness of the A.I. moment.
snippet: The Shoggoth, a character from a science fiction story, captures the essential weirdness of the A.I. moment.
lead_paragraph: A few months ago, while meeting with an A.I. executive in San Francisco, I spotted a strange sticker on his laptop. The sticker depicted a cartoon of a menacing, octopus-like creature with many eyes and a yellow smiley-face attached to one of its tentacles. I asked what it was.

main: Why an Octopus-like Creature Has Come to Symbolize the State of A.I.
print_headline: This Meme Symbolizes  State of A.I.

abstract: A proposal to end a decade-long attempt to seek the death penalty before a military tribunal carries political risks, but the Trump administration also decided the system failed.
snippet: A proposal to end a decade-long attempt to seek the death penalty before a military tribunal carries political risks, but the Trump administration also decided the system failed.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Across four presidencies, the question of how to obtain a measure of justice in court for the attacks of Sept. 11, 2001, has vexed American officials. A military tribunal case against five Guantánamo Bay detainees accused of conspiring with the hijackers has spun its wheels for more than a decade with no trial in sight.

main: Biden Leery of Involvement in Potential Plea Deal in Sept. 11 Case
print_headline: Biden Leery of a Role  In a Possible Plea Deal  With Five 9/11 Suspects

original: By Charlie Savage and Carol Rosenberg

abstract: For the first time, the National Rally is the main opposition party in Parliament. But can it use its new perch to convince voters it has changed?

lead_paragraph: PARIS — French lawmakers erupted in turmoil last week when a member of Parliament from the far right interrupted a Black colleague’s speech about shipwrecked migrants in the Mediterranean by shouting, “Back to Africa!”

main: An Outburst Threatens the French Far Right’s Effort to Go Mainstream
print_headline: Outburst Threatens France Far Right’s Push

abstract: You asked, we answered your questions about the weight of following a smash single and the persistence of genre.
snippet: You asked, we answered your questions about the weight of following a smash single and the persistence of genre.
lead_paragraph: The Popcast crew assembles for a semiannual mailbag episode, touching on many of the pressing pop music issues of the moment, including the controversy surrounding Frank Ocean’s Coachella set; the challenges faced by even the biggest pop stars (Sam Smith, Miley Cyrus) trying to follow massive singles; the sudden arrival of artificial intelligence in pop music and evolving notions of authorship; the startling recent growth in the popularity and visibility of música Mexicana and corridos tumbados, with stars like Grupo Frontera and Peso Pluma; and how the framework of genre continues to have meaning even in a universal-jukebox universe.

main: Popcast Mailbag! Frank Ocean, Peso Pluma, A.I. Grimes and More

abstract: After a miserable year, cryptocurrency companies are looking for ways to rebrand products that many consumers no longer trust.
